Subject: [osmo-bts] Force setattr_success on Radio Carrier OPSTART for BSC/BTS version skew
Date: 2026-05-26
Applies-to: osmo-bts 1.10.0
Tested-with: osmo-bsc 1.14.0
Author: Calypso QEMU pipeline (manual workaround)

PROBLEM
-------
With osmo-bsc 1.14.0 driving osmo-bts 1.10.0, the BSC issues an OML
Get-Attributes-Request for the Radio Carrier MO that lists attributes
the BTS does not support (SW Configuration on RADIO-CARRIER, Manufacturer
Dependent State on BASEBAND-TRANSCEIVER, SW Configuration on GPRS-CELL).
The BTS replies with NM_NACK_OBJCLASS_NOTSUPP per attribute, and the BSC
then never sends a Set-Radio-Attributes message. Consequently
`trx->mo.setattr_success` stays at its init value `false`, and when the
BSC subsequently sends OPSTART for the Radio Carrier, the FSM emits
`oml_mo_opstart_nack(&trx->mo, NM_NACK_CANT_PERFORM)` and the BSC drops
the OML link. The cycle repeats forever ; the BTS scheduler never enters
OP_ENABLED for the radio carrier, so TS0 is configured but never radiated
as FCCH/SCH/BCCH — only DUMMY NB fills the slot.

EVIDENCE
--------
- BSC log : `OPSTART NACK CAUSE=Message cannot be performed` on every
  RADIO-CARRIER OPSTART try, followed by `Got OPSTART NACK going to drop
  the OML links`.
- BTS log : `DOML ERROR OC=RADIO-CARRIER : O&M Get Attributes [0], SW
  Configuration is unsupported`.
- BTS log : `grep -c NM_EV_ /tmp/bts.log` returns 0 → no
  NM_EV_RX_SETATTR ever delivered to the radio_carrier FSM.
- FFT sweep on 51 consecutive DL chunks (tools/fcch_sweep.py) : zero
  bursts with dphi_std<0.10 ; all 51 chunks have dphi_std≈1.10 and
  full-scale rms ≈ 32000 — signature of GMSK-modulated DUMMY NB
  (alternating ±π/2 phase steps), not FCCH (constant +π/2).

WORKAROUND
----------
Inside `nm_radio_carrier_fsm.c::st_op_disabled_offline()`, on
`NM_EV_RX_OPSTART`, force `trx->mo.setattr_success = true` instead of
checking it. This mirrors the existing `#if 0` block in
`nm_bb_transc_fsm.c` that upstream already used to handle the same class
of issue for the BASEBAND-TRANSCEIVER object ("Disabled because osmo-bsc
doesn't send SetAttr on BB_TRANSC object").

Setting `setattr_success=true` also unblocks the later recalc check
`rsl_link && phy_state && setattr_success && opstart_success` that
transitions the FSM to OP_ENABLED.

The BTS 1.10 has nothing to apply from these unsupported attrs anyway,
so bypassing the gate does not cause a configuration loss — it just
restores the operational path that the version skew has artificially
blocked.

LONG-TERM
---------
Proper fix is to align versions (osmo-bsc 1.10.x with osmo-bts 1.10, or
upgrade osmo-bts to a release that reports the attrs the BSC 1.14
queries). This patch is a localized workaround until then.

---
 src/common/nm_radio_carrier_fsm.c | 12 ++++++++----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/src/common/nm_radio_carrier_fsm.c
+++ b/src/common/nm_radio_carrier_fsm.c
@@ -122,10 +122,14 @@
 		oml_fom_ack_nack_copy_msg(setattr_data->msg, rc);
 		break; /* check statechg below */
 	case NM_EV_RX_OPSTART:
-		if (!trx->mo.setattr_success) {
-			oml_mo_opstart_nack(&trx->mo, NM_NACK_CANT_PERFORM);
-			return;
-		}
+		/* Workaround 2026-05-26 : osmo-bsc 1.14 + osmo-bts 1.10 version skew.
+		 * BSC queries OML attrs unsupported by BTS (SW Configuration,
+		 * Manufacturer Dep State on Radio Carrier) → BSC skips SetAttr
+		 * → setattr_success stays false → NACK loop. Mirrors the existing
+		 * #if 0 in nm_bb_transc_fsm.c that disabled the same check for the
+		 * BB_TRANSC object. Force setattr_success=true so the subsequent
+		 * state recalc (rsl && phy && setattr && opstart) can pass too. */
+		trx->mo.setattr_success = true;
 		bts_model_opstart(trx->bts, &trx->mo, trx);
 		return;
 	case NM_EV_OPSTART_ACK:
